The paper discusses reinforcement learning algorithms with linear function approximation, which is a common technique in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the convergence rate and sample complexity, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of minimax variants suggests that the paper may also be relevant to game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper's focus on finite-sample analysis suggests that it may be relevant to the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
